The flight resumed its journey to San Diego - taking off from Denver at 9:30 pm yesterday. JetBlue  is reportedly treating the incident as a customer service issue and no charges have been filed.

JetBlue mainly serves destinations within the United States, along with flights to the Caribbean, and Latin America. Its main base is John F. Kennedy International Airport in New York.

The American budget airline has not released any more information about the incident,

